# Release

## Purpose

This repo uses a lightweight release helper for tagging and pushing documented releases.

## Canonical Command

```bash
go run ./cmd/rel vX.Y.Z "<concrete release message>"
```

## Shell Convenience

If the repo includes `rel.sh`, the same release can be triggered with:

```bash
./rel.sh vX.Y.Z "<concrete release message>"
```

## Notes

- the release message must summarize the real changes in the release, not use a generic label
- the command always asks for interactive confirmation
- the only supported option is help: `-h`, `-?`, or `--help`
